Share of occupations covered by new standards out of total number of occupationsin the priority sectors supported by the project
Share of project schools with established boards (with participation of employers).
Formula-based financing mechanism piloted in one or two regions.
Plan developed for nationwide implementation of formula-based financing.
An evaluation study completed and report generated.
Concept of NQS and NQF approved by GOK and employers.
Formula-based financing policy options studied and proposal developed.
Implementation plan for the governance and management improvement prepared, budgeted, and adopted by MOES.
Legal framework, includingregulations, revised andapproved by GOK.
NQF and key elements of NQS formally adopted by the GOK.
Study completed on governance and management of TVE at all levels with policy options generated.
Share of project schools that introduced programs that use competency-based curriculum.
Share of teachers in each project school trained indeveloping and delivering new CBT programs.
Number of project schools that passed independent institutional accreditation (at least one school from eachof 10 priority sectors).
Share of the existing programs in the projects supported schools revised in accordance with the newly introduced competency standards.
Share of private TVE institutions that received grants (out of schools that received grants).
Number of educational standards updated in line with occupational standards.
Number of updated educational standards supported with revised core curriculum.
Share of lyceums/colleges that received grants (out of total number).
Number of in-service teacher-training programs developed in the area of CBT (progressive total).
Employer satisfaction with industry-led competency standards as a basis for development of curriculum and programs.
Share of schools that implement the grants in accordance with the targets set in their IDPs (out of schools that received grants).
National and sector councils have at least one-third of members from the industry.
Number of priority (10) sectors which established councils.
